description:
&lt;p&gt;Are you looking to lead?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a highly motivated individual to apply for the role of band 7 Sister/Charge Nurse. Ward 22 is an acute ward, specialising Gastroenterology Medicine. We are seeking an exceptional and experienced leader with excellent clinical skills, to join our band 7 Senior Nurse Leadership team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a forward thinking, enthusiastic and innovative nurse who will be able to lead and motivate nursing staff in the provision of high quality patient focussed care. The successful candidate will be enthusiastic and friendly and be able to demonstrate clinical leadership skills. The successful candidate needs to be passionate about staff and patient experience and wellbeing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post offers huge potential for further developing your clinical, leadership and management skills in a challenging but supportive setting. The successful candidate will need to confidently manage and provide strong leadership, training and education for all staff, ensuring their involvement in the development of the service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are committed to the development and application of high quality patient care we want to hear from you!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Emma Wilson - Matron&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: emma.wilson28@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 01623 622515 ext 4678 or 07785485650&lt;/p&gt;
